title: Vermont Center for Geographic Information, High Accident Locations (Point), Vermont, 1986-1990
name: Vermont Center for Geographic Information, High Accident Locations (Point), Vermont, 1986-1990
description:
Each arc of this coverage corresponds to a high accident
      location (HAL), based on a VTrans database with the
      location of each HAL given by milemarkers along named
      routes (the database was provided by the VTrans in June
      1994).  The arcs were generated by linking the HALs
      milemarkers to the RDS\RDSRT route system (which was
      extracted from the TransRoad_RDS road centerline data).  Several
      HALs not occuring on state-system highways were
      manually located.
    Purpose: High Accident Locations, 1986-1990
Please search for Vermont-GIS for more   local level GIS datasets.
